# Reflection

This assignment focused on system design and interaction modeling.One challenge was understanding how components communicate within the system. 
Translating earlier requirements and activity diagrams into sequence diagrams required careful mapping.

Another challenge was designing the class diagram to accurately represent system structure without making it overly complex. 
It was important to balance simplicity and completeness.

Sequence diagrams helped visualize how users interact with the system step-by-step, while the class diagram provided a structural view of the system.
Together, these diagrams improved understanding of both system behavior and architecture.

Overall, this assignment strengthened understanding of system design and how different components interact in a real-world application.

